avlcal
------------------------------------------
AvlCal aims at providing a clean API and a simple implementation (C++ library)
of an Airline-related Seat Inventory Availability Calculation system. That
library uses the Standard Airline IT C++ object model
(https://github.com/airsim/stdair).

Runtime requirements:
  bash-5.2.21-1
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libavlcal-devel-1.00.8-1bl1
  libavlcal1.00-1.00.8-1bl1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libstdair1.00-1.00.26-1bl1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  doxygen-1.17.0-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libstdair-devel-1.00.26-1bl1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/airsim/avlcal

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/airsim/avlcal/archive/refs/tags/v1.00.8.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack avlcal-1.00.8-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./avlcal-1.00.8-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/avlcal-1.00.8-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/avlcal-1.00.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libavlcal1.00-1.00.8-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libavlcal-devel-1.00.8-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(avlcal)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/avlcal.README
  /usr/share/doc/avlcal/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/avlcal/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/avlcal/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/avlcal/NEWS
  /usr/share/doc/avlcal/README.md

(libavlcal1.00)
  /usr/bin/cygavlcal-1.00.dll

(libavlcal-devel)
  /usr/bin/avlcal-config
  /usr/include/avlcal/AVLCAL_Service.hpp
  /usr/include/avlcal/AVLCAL_Types.hpp
  /usr/lib/cmake/avlcal/avlcal-config-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/avlcal/avlcal-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/avlcal/avlcal-library-depends-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/avlcal/avlcal-library-depends.cmake
  /usr/lib/libavlcal.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/avlcal.pc
  /usr/share/aclocal/avlcal.m4

